[normal]5.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]See also response to Q1.  Government has frequently been t
[normal]oo slow and too privat
[normal]e
[normal],
[normal] not least because Chief Scientific Advisers are only loosely tied in to top level strategy and planning i
[normal]n many Departments. There is a general flaw 
[normal]within
[normal] Departments
[normal] of
[normal] having too few external advisory bodies
[normal].  These tend to be 
[normal]relatively
[normal] informal bodies operating at about Deputy Director level
[normal],
[normal] discuss
[normal]ing
[normal] technology movements, 
[normal]industry 
[normal]trends and
[normal] 
[normal]scientific developments and thus acting as the very early 
[normal]detectors of issues where a more structured approach would be justified.  There are particular
[normal] problems in Transport where the fact that delivery rests with Local Authorities and Industry has been s
[normal]een as a reason to justify too much inactivity regarding tactical technology thinking.
